n Peru C. a. sordidum - (Berlepsch, 1901): Junín in Peru to La Paz in Bolivia C. a. lugens - (Berlepsch, 1901): Yungas of eastern Bolivia Description The capped conebill is 13-14 cm long and weighs 11.7-21.5 g. Males in the \"albifrons\" group sport a white crown, with a slaty-black face, breast, and neck; a liberty blue shoulder and tail; and a navy blue back. Males in the \"atrocyaneum\" group have a deep blue cap, back, wing, and tail; a glaucous shoulder; and a slaty breast, neck, and face. Females have a light blue crown, a blue-grey head, a dark yellow body, and an olive back and wings. Both sexes have a slightly-curved black bill and grey legs. Distribution & habitat The capped conebill ranges from a separate population in Venezuela around the state of Miranda, through the Andes from Colombia to Peru, and then into the Yungas of Peru and Bolivia. It inhabits tropical montane cloud forest from 2000-2800 m. Status The capped conebill is currently assessed as Least Concern by the IUCN, though its population is suspected to be decreasing. References", "shortSummary": "The capped conebill (Conirostrum albifrons) is a species of bird in the family Thraupidae. It is found in Bolivia, Colombia, Ecuador, Peru,…", "locations": ["玻利維亞", "哥伦比亚", "厄瓜多尔", "委內瑞拉", "云雾森林"], "lat": -16.712, "lng": -64.666, "imageUrl": "https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/82/Capped_Conebill_-_Ecuador_S4E4700_%2822882391489%29.jpg/960px-Capped_Conebill_-_Ecuador_S4E4700_%2822882391489%29.jpg", "kingdomId": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylumId": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "classId": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genusId": "taxonomy-genus-conirostrum", "speciesId": "taxonomy-species-conirostrum-albifrons", "taxonomyIds": {"kingdom": "taxonomy-kingdom-animalia", "phylum": "taxonomy-phylum-chordata", "class": "taxonomy-class-aves", "genus": "taxonomy-genus-conirostrum", "species": "taxonomy-species-conirostrum-albifrons"}, "expandable": true, "x": -113.11, "y": 647.64, "z": -388.2},